        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-07-31T18:50:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-04-14T18:51:00-05:00" n="123" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d123">
                <head>Fraternity of the People Lodge</head>
                <dateline>
                    <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-volume-rules" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1865-07-31T23:59:59+00:09" notBefore="1865-04-15T00:00:00+00:09">undated</date>
                </dateline>
                <note rend="inline" rendition="#center" type="source">[Translation.]</note>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="italic">Address of the Lodge of the Fraternity of the People, in
                            the east of Paris, to the American Free Masons, on the occasion of the
                            death of Mr. Lincoln</hi>.</p>
                <p>The Loge la Fraternité des Peuples has profoundly felt the great grief which
                        has agitated the world on the receipt of the news of the horrible outrage to
                        which F** Lincoln has fallen a victim. F** of America, the masons of France
                            <pb facs="0151" n="79" xml:id="pg_79"/> lament the irreparable loss of
                        the virtuous citizen, of the great politician; but they know that with them
                        and by them slavery will be annihilated, and that the sacred cause of
                        liberty will shine forth in a great triumph which is at hand, a glorious
                        compensation for the deep grief of this sad period.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>E. DENISE, </signed>
                    <hi rend="italic">Ven</hi>. **.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
